## Room And Architecture

The scene is an L-shaped kitchen in a room corner, with raw wall/ceiling geometry present. The room dimensions are explicitly annotated:

- Long left/tall wall: `4339`.
- Back wall run: `2564`.
- Room height / top references: `2558`, `2248`, and furniture top zones around `2218`, `2438`, `2530` depending on module family.

Pattern: raw room faces and dimension entities are first-class design evidence. The generator must read wall axes and ceiling/top constraints before placing modules.

## Layout Composition

This is not the same pattern as the previous Margit U-like scene. Sven is a compact L with a tall appliance bank on the left leg and the working sink/fridge run on the back wall.

### Left/Tall Leg

Top-level chain along the left leg (`X[0..671]`, negative Y):

- `PB2#3`: `Y[-4289..-3789]`, 500mm wide tall module.
- `PB2#2`: `Y[-3789..-3289]`, 500mm wide tall module.
- `PD1_6#1`: `Y[-3289..-2689]`, 600mm oven/micro pencil.
- `Wine Fridge`: `Y[-2665.2..-2370]`, low wine appliance next to tall bank.
- `BD2#1`: `Y[-2351..-1496]`, 855mm drawer base.
- `BD2_1#1`: `Y[-1496..-641]`, 855mm cooktop base.
- `BG1#3`: corner module at `X[0..1177]`, `Y[-670..0]`.

The left leg uses a 50mm terminal strip at the far end, two 500mm tall modules, then a 600mm oven pencil, then a 300mm wine-fridge visual/appliance slot, then 19mm panel transition before the lower run.

### Back/Sink/Fridge Row

Back row chain (`Y[-671..0]`):

- `BG1#3`: corner start, `X[0..1177]` with dimension intent `50+535`.
- `BD1`: sink base, `X[1177..1777]`, 600mm.
- `BI#1`: dishwasher, `X[1777..2377]`, 600mm.
- `BJ`: narrow/filler module, `X[2377.1..2602.1]`, observed 225mm, dimension intent includes `150` near this zone.
- `PB3F#2`: integrated fridge/tall module, `X[2527..3127]`, 600mm, full height `Z[0..2530]`.
- `PANEL-FACADE#3`: right full-height side panel, 19.3mm thick, `Z[0..2530]`.

Pattern: integrated fridge/tall module can terminate a back row; countertop must stop before the fridge/pencil zone. Dimension entities encode the row chain: `50+535`, `600`, `600`, `150`, `600`, `19`.

## Corner And Junction Logic

Only one real lower corner is used: `BG1#3` at the inside L turn. It joins the back row and left leg, instead of synthesizing the corner from straight cabinets.

Learning rule: compact L scenes may use one `BG1` plus asymmetric straight modules around it. The dimension label `50+535` near the corner should be preserved as intent, not simplified to a generic 600.

## Appliances And Services

- Cooktop: `Miele KM 6322 PowerFlex`, over `BD2_1#1` on the left leg, bbox `X[53..567]`, `Y[-1350.5..-735.5]`, `Z[900..910]`.
- Oven: `Miele H6461`, in `PD1_6#1`, bbox `X[72..670]`, `Y[-3287..-2691]`, `Z[476.8..1068.5]`.
- Microwave/upper appliance: `Samsung`, above oven in `PD1_6#1`, bbox `X[256.3..676.3]`, `Y[-3287.7..-2692.7]`, `Z[1068.5..1454.8]`.
- Wine fridge: existing component, bbox `X[20..657.4]`, `Y[-2665.2..-2370]`, `Z[5..878.1]`.
- Sink: over `BD1`, bbox `X[1261..1711]`, `Y[-585..-75]`, `Z[673..903]`.
- Mixer: `Group30#1`, bbox `X[1452.9..1564.3]`, `Y[-314.9..-65.7]`, `Z[900..1235.3]`.

Pattern: this scene separates cooktop base and oven pencil. Do not infer oven-under-cooktop when the design uses `PD1_6` for the oven/micro stack.

## Fridge Rule Evidence

`PB3F#2` is an integrated fridge/tall module, not a standalone-fridge niche. The separate `Wine Fridge` confirms that visual appliance components may be kept in the scene when they represent real appliances. For future standalone-fridge openings, use existing fridge components from the available component library; do not create separate measuring geometry.

## Panels, Fillers, And Cladding

Top-level `PANEL-FACADE` roles include:

- Tall side/end panels: `PANEL-FACADE#3`, `#4`, `#5`, `#6`.
- Toe/plinth or low front strips: `PANEL-FACADE#7`, `#8`, `#9` with low heights around 128/138mm and long runs.
- Detached sample/side panels visible outside the main kitchen footprint: `PANEL-FACADE#1`, `#2`.

Pattern: classify `PANEL-FACADE` by bbox and adjacency, not only by name. This scene reinforces the multi-role panel rule from Margit.

## Countertops And Work Zones

Four countertop-like components were found:

- Main back worktop: `X[590..2508]`, `Y[-650..0]`, `Z[862..900]`.
- Left leg worktop: `X[0..650]`, `Y[-2351..10]`, `Z[862..900]`.
- Vertical backsplash/upstand-like slab on back: `X[-0.2..2507.8]`, `Y[-10..0]`, `Z[850..1500]`.
- Vertical backsplash/upstand-like slab on left: `X[-0.2..9.8]`, `Y[-2351..-10]`, `Z[850..1500]`.

Pattern: worktops remain straight segments, and backsplash/upstand objects may share the countertop definition/kind. Verification must distinguish horizontal worktop from vertical backsplash by bbox orientation.

## Upper And Lighting Pattern

Upper row uses mixed upper widths:

- Back row: `TA` 420mm, then `TB1` modules around 494mm, with high `Z[1500..2530]`.
- Left row: `TB2-H3#1` 856mm, then two `TB1#2` modules of 428mm.
- LED/profile components run under uppers on both legs (`Врезной профиль для подсветки`).

Pattern: upper layout follows lower/corner geometry but uses its own width sequence; do not force upper widths to mirror lower modules one-to-one.

## Dimensions Worth Preserving

Dimension texts: `2564`, `4339`, `2248`, `2558`, `19`, `600`, `150`, `600`, `600`, `50+535`, `855+49`, `500`, `500`, `50`, `606`, `420`, `494`, `494`, `494`, `1030`, `600`, `38`, `770`, `92`, `392`, `2438`, `28`, `855`, `2126`, `30`, `300`, `639`, `856`, `428`, `428`.

Important recurring standards:

- Base system: `92` legs + `770` carcass + `38` countertop = `900` working top.
- Full-height side/end panels: 19mm.
- Tall module sequence includes 500/500/600 widths.
- Back row module sequence includes corner intent `50+535`, then 600/600/150/600/19.

